<collectingCountry id="F33E760BFFA8E2753126A8F7FBDEFC7A" box="[1028,1127,907,933]" name="Ethiopia" pageId="8" pageNumber="530">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B96369BFFA8E27535E5A8D3FB93FBA2" blockId="8.[151,1437,150,1149]" pageId="8" pageNumber="530">
Differential diagnosis. 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D18FFA8E27534E9A8D3FD5CFC16" authority="Bílý, 2020" authorityName="Bílý" authorityYear="2020" box="[459,741,943,969]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="530" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aethiopica" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFA8E27534E9A8D3FD89FC16" box="[459,560,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="530">Anthaxia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFA8E2753760A8D3FDE4FC17" box="[578,605,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="530">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFA8E275374DA8D3FD5CFC16" box="[623,741,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="530">aethiopica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFA8E27537CFA8D3FCF1FC16" bold="true" box="[749,840,943,969]" pageId="8" pageNumber="530">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26E57F2FFA8E27537CFA8D3FCF1FC16" box="[749,840,943,969]" pageId="8" pageNumber="530" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is rather similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D18FFA8E275310BA8D3FB71FC16" authorityName="Kerremans" authorityYear="1898" box="[1065,1224,943,969]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="530" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dispar" subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFA8E275310BA8D3FBFBFC16" box="[1065,1090,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="530">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFA8E2753171A8D3FBD6FC17" box="[1107,1135,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="530">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFA8E27531A2A8D3FB71FC16" box="[1152,1224,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="530">dispar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from which it differs by the shorter frontal pubescence, simply punctured pronotal disc, much smaller tarsal claws, weakly wider pronotum and longer elytra (se the key) and somewhat by the different male metatibiae (
<figureCitation id="13122A1EFFA8E275314EA88BFB05FBCE" box="[1132,1212,1015,1041]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="9.[151,212,1917,1941]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,1318,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-459@9.[151,1435,1317,1894]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGS. 23–28. Male metatibiae (not in scale). 23—Anthaxia (Haplathaxia) aethiopica sp. nov., holotype; 24—A. (H.) caerulea sp. nov., holotype; 25—A. (H.) dispar Kerremans, 1898 (RSA, Limpopo); 26—A. (H.) keniae Théry, 1941 (Kenya, Kiserian); 27—A. (H.) occidentalis sp. nov., holotype; 28—A. (H.) pilifrons Kerremans, 1898, holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4408017" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4408017/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="530">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
) and aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="13122A1EFFA8E275304DA88BFF0FFBE9" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="8.[151,212,1796,1820]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,1174,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-414@8.[151,1436,1173,1773]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGS. 16–22. Aedeagi (not in scale). 16—Anthaxia (Haplathaxia) aethiopica sp. nov., holotype; 17—A. (H.) caerulea sp. nov., holotype; 18—A. (H.) dispar Kerremans, 1898 (RSA, Limpopo); 19—A. (H.) keniae Théry, 1941 (Kenya, Kiserian); 20—A. (H.) komareki Obenberger, 1931, holotype; 21—A. (H.) occidentalis sp. nov., holotype; 22—A. (H.) pilifrons Kerremans, 1898, holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4408013" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4408013/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="530">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
). Another very similar species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D18FFA8E275373BAF67FD4DFBEA" authority="Bílý, 2020" authorityName="Bílý" authorityYear="2020" box="[537,756,1051,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="530" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="occidentalis" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFA8E275373BAF67FD88FBEA" box="[537,561,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="530">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFA8E2753763AF67FDE4FBEB" box="[577,605,1051,1076]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="530">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFA8E275374FAF67FD4DFBEA" box="[621,756,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="530">occidentalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFA8E27537D9AF67FCE5FBEA" bold="true" box="[763,860,1051,1077]" pageId="8" pageNumber="530">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26E57F2FFA8E27537D9AF67FCEFFBEA" box="[763,854,1051,1077]" pageId="8" pageNumber="530" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
,
</emphasis>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D18FFA8E27536D2AF67FB03FBEA" authority="Bílý, 2020" authorityName="Bílý" authorityYear="2020" box="[1008,1210,1051,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="530" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aethiopica" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFA8E27536D2AF67FBB1FBEA" box="[1008,1032,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="530">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFA8E275313AAF67FB8DFBEB" box="[1048,1076,1051,1076]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="530">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFA8E2753166AF67FB03FBEA" box="[1092,1210,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="530">aethiopica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFA8E27531E3AF67FAA2FBEA" bold="true" box="[1217,1307,1051,1077]" pageId="8" pageNumber="530">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26E57F2FFA8E27531E3AF67FAA2FBEA" box="[1217,1307,1051,1077]" pageId="8" pageNumber="530" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(except for the distribution) by the flat frons, longer frontal pubescence, weakly transverse sculpture of the pronotal disc, larger tarsal claws and by the shape of male metatibiae (
<figureCitation id="13122A1EFFA8E27537E6AF1FFCACFBA2" box="[708,789,1123,1149]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="9.[151,212,1917,1941]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,1318,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-459@9.[151,1435,1317,1894]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGS. 23–28. Male metatibiae (not in scale). 23—Anthaxia (Haplathaxia) aethiopica sp. nov., holotype; 24—A. (H.) caerulea sp. nov., holotype; 25—A. (H.) dispar Kerremans, 1898 (RSA, Limpopo); 26—A. (H.) keniae Théry, 1941 (Kenya, Kiserian); 27—A. (H.) occidentalis sp. nov., holotype; 28—A. (H.) pilifrons Kerremans, 1898, holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4408017" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4408017/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="530">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
) and aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="13122A1EFFA8E27536E8AF1FFBA4FBA2" box="[970,1053,1123,1149]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="8.[151,212,1796,1820]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,1174,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-414@8.[151,1436,1173,1773]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGS. 16–22. Aedeagi (not in scale). 16—Anthaxia (Haplathaxia) aethiopica sp. nov., holotype; 17—A. (H.) caerulea sp. nov., holotype; 18—A. (H.) dispar Kerremans, 1898 (RSA, Limpopo); 19—A. (H.) keniae Théry, 1941 (Kenya, Kiserian); 20—A. (H.) komareki Obenberger, 1931, holotype; 21—A. (H.) occidentalis sp. nov., holotype; 22—A. (H.) pilifrons Kerremans, 1898, holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4408013" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4408013/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="530">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
